					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">2 tilemaps ? Blending ? What's the point ?<br /><br />In all cases, if you use mode 4, you can get a second tilemap with 2BP tiles. A complete image with it takes 16k + 1k for the map.<br />If you use this, the space remaining for the 8BP tiles of BG 0 is 64k - 1k - 16 - 1k = 46k = 736 tiles = 23 tile rows. Not quite fullscreen, but not too far away.<br /><br />Since this also means less tiles will be used for the second tilemap, a compromise could be found between 23 and 30 rows.</div>

