				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Mode 4 has the &quot;offset-per-tile&quot; mode that mode 3 lacks.<br /><br />You can't save VRAM by using mosaic, period. Remember how tiles are stored in memory, each byte is a &quot;bitplane&quot; of 8-pixel.<br />What you'd do by setting the mosaic to 2 is make every odd bit in all bytes of VRAM unused, but there is no way to use those bits in any way.<br /><br />And I really don't think you'd notice if there is more than 256 colours or not, given the assumption that the 256 colours have been well chosen.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

